<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> Plutarch, <i>Apophthegmata Laconica,</i> 225d.13.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBradford2004"><a href="/wiki/Ernle_Bradford" title="Ernle Bradford">Bradford, Ernle</a> (2004-03-30). <i><a href="http://www.perseusbooksgroup.com/dacapo/book_detail.jsp?isbn=0306813602" class="external text" title="http://www.perseusbooksgroup.com/dacapo/book_detail.jsp?isbn=0306813602" rel="nofollow">Thermopylae: The Battle for the West</a></i>. New York: Da Capo Press. p.&#160;141. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0306813602" class="internal">ISBN 0306813602</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.perseusbooksgroup.com/dacapo/book_detail.jsp?isbn=0306813602" class="external free" title="http://www.perseusbooksgroup.com/dacapo/book_detail.jsp?isbn=0306813602" rel="nofollow">http://www.perseusbooksgroup.com/dacapo/book_detail.jsp?isbn=0306813602</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Thermopylae%3A+The+Battle+for+the+West&amp;rft.aulast=Bradford&amp;rft.aufirst=Ernle&amp;rft.au=Bradford%2C+Ernle&amp;rft.date=2004-03-30&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B141&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Da+Capo+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0306813602&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.perseusbooksgroup.com%2Fdacapo%2Fbook_detail.jsp%3Fisbn%3D0306813602&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Plutarch, <i>Apophthegmata Laconica,</i> 230f.6.</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Herodotus" title="Herodotus">Herodotus</a> <a href="/wiki/Histories_(Herodotus)" title="Histories (Herodotus)">The Histories</a>, Book 3, section 46.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGarland1998">Garland, Robert (1998-08-30). <i><a href="http://www.greenwood.com/catalog/GR0383.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.greenwood.com/catalog/GR0383.aspx" rel="nofollow">Daily Life of the Ancient Greeks</a></i>. Westport, Connecticut: Greenwood Press. p.&#160;81. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1336%2F0313303835" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1336%2F0313303835" rel="nofollow">10.1336/0313303835</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0313303835" class="internal">ISBN 0313303835</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.greenwood.com/catalog/GR0383.aspx" class="external free" title="http://www.greenwood.com/catalog/GR0383.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://www.greenwood.com/catalog/GR0383.aspx</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Daily+Life+of+the+Ancient+Greeks&amp;rft.aulast=Garland&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Garland%2C+Robert&amp;rft.date=1998-08-30&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B81&amp;rft.place=Westport%2C+Connecticut&amp;rft.pub=Greenwood+Press&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1336%2F0313303835&amp;rft.isbn=0313303835&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greenwood.com%2Fcatalog%2FGR0383.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.attalus.org/old/demetrius2.html" class="external free" title="http://www.attalus.org/old/demetrius2.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.attalus.org/old/demetrius2.html</a> <a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a>: Life of Demetrius</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.pbs.org/empires/thegreeks/background/8c_p1.html" class="external free" title="http://www.pbs.org/empires/thegreeks/background/8c_p1.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.pbs.org/empires/thegreeks/background/8c_p1.html</a> PBS</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> Plutarch, <i><a href="/wiki/Parallel_Lives" title="Parallel Lives">Parallel Lives</a></i>, <a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Lives_(Dryden_translation)/Phocion" class="external text" title="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Lives_(Dryden_translation)/Phocion" rel="nofollow">"Phocion"</a>, 16.6.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://ghostwolf.dyndns.org/words/authors/P/Plutarch/prose/plutachslives/pyrrhus.html" class="external free" title="http://ghostwolf.dyndns.org/words/authors/P/Plutarch/prose/plutachslives/pyrrhus.html" rel="nofollow">http://ghostwolf.dyndns.org/words/authors/P/Plutarch/prose/plutachslives/pyrrhus.html</a> <a href="/wiki/Plutarch" title="Plutarch">Plutarch</a>: Life of Pyrrhus</li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Julius_Caesar" title="Julius Caesar">Julius Caesar</a>, <a href="/wiki/Commentarii_de_Bello_Gallico" title="Commentarii de Bello Gallico">The Gallic Wars</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> The <a href="http://old-russian.chat.ru/02povest.htm" class="external text" title="http://old-russian.chat.ru/02povest.htm" rel="nofollow">Russian Primary Chronicle</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=0LFKGVQFf2sC&amp;pg=PA78&amp;lpg=PA78&amp;dq=%22genghis+khan%22+%22you+have+chosen+war%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=xZXCkeyy1V&amp;sig=L2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s#PPA78,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=0LFKGVQFf2sC&amp;pg=PA78&amp;lpg=PA78&amp;dq=%22genghis+khan%22+%22you+have+chosen+war%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=xZXCkeyy1V&amp;sig=L2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s#PPA78,M1" rel="nofollow">"How Great Generals Win: A Military ... - Google Book Search:"</a>. books.google.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=0LFKGVQFf2sC&amp;pg=PA78&amp;lpg=PA78&amp;dq=%22genghis+khan%22+%22you+have+chosen+war%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=xZXCkeyy1V&amp;sig=L2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s#PPA78,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=0LFKGVQFf2sC&amp;pg=PA78&amp;lpg=PA78&amp;dq=%22genghis+khan%22+%22you+have+chosen+war%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=xZXCkeyy1V&amp;sig=L2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s#PPA78,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=0LFKGVQFf2sC&amp;pg=PA78&amp;lpg=PA78&amp;dq=%22genghis+khan%22+%22you+have+chosen+war%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=xZXCkeyy1V&amp;sig=L2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s#PPA78,M1</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-03-17</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=How+Great+Generals+Win%3A+A+Military+...+-+Google+Book+Search%3A&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=books.google.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D0LFKGVQFf2sC%26pg%3DPA78%26lpg%3DPA78%26dq%3D%2522genghis%2Bkhan%2522%2B%2522you%2Bhave%2Bchosen%2Bwar%2522%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3DxZXCkeyy1V%26sig%3DL2Th6SNfvceAyB1JASXGkrkyC6s%23PPA78%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFNeiberg2009">Neiberg, Michael (2003), <i>Foch: Supreme Allied Commander in the Great War</i>, Brassey's, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/157488672X" class="internal">ISBN 157488672X</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Foch%3A+Supreme+Allied+Commander+in+the+Great+War&amp;rft.aulast=Neiberg&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft.au=Neiberg%2C+Michael&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Brassey%27s&amp;rft.isbn=157488672X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFNicholas">Nicholas, Jeremy. <a href="http://www.godowsky.com/Biography/humor.html" class="external text" title="http://www.godowsky.com/Biography/humor.html" rel="nofollow">"Wit and Wisdom"</a>. <i>www.godowsky.com</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.godowsky.com/Biography/humor.html" class="external free" title="http://www.godowsky.com/Biography/humor.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.godowsky.com/Biography/humor.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-10-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Wit+and+Wisdom&amp;rft.atitle=www.godowsky.com&amp;rft.aulast=Nicholas&amp;rft.aufirst=Jeremy&amp;rft.au=Nicholas%2C+Jeremy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.godowsky.com%2FBiography%2Fhumor.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCoolidge2009">Coolidge, Calvin (2001), Hannaford, Peter, ed., <i><a href="http://www.imagesfromthepast.com/coolidge.html" class="external text" title="http://www.imagesfromthepast.com/coolidge.html" rel="nofollow">The Quotable Calvin Coolidge: Sensible Words for a New Century</a></i>, Bennington, Vermont: Images From the Past, pp.&#160;169, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1884592333" class="internal">ISBN 1884592333</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.imagesfromthepast.com/coolidge.html" class="external free" title="http://www.imagesfromthepast.com/coolidge.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.imagesfromthepast.com/coolidge.html</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Quotable+Calvin+Coolidge%3A+Sensible+Words+for+a+New+Century&amp;rft.aulast=Coolidge&amp;rft.aufirst=Calvin&amp;rft.au=Coolidge%2C+Calvin&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B169&amp;rft.place=Bennington%2C+Vermont&amp;rft.pub=Images+From+the+Past&amp;rft.isbn=1884592333&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.imagesfromthepast.com%2Fcoolidge.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> This began early. When Dirac was a child, his authoritarian father, a teacher of French, enforced a rule that Dirac speak to him only in French, as a device to encourage him to learn the language. But since young Dirac had difficulty expressing himself in French, the result was he spoke very little.</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFDirac">Dirac, Gisela. <a href="http://www.dirac.ch/PaulDirac.html" class="external text" title="http://www.dirac.ch/PaulDirac.html" rel="nofollow">"Paul Adrien Maurice Dirac (1902-1984)"</a>. <i>DIRAC Family Research</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.dirac.ch/PaulDirac.html" class="external free" title="http://www.dirac.ch/PaulDirac.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.dirac.ch/PaulDirac.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-10-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Paul+Adrien+Maurice+Dirac+%281902-1984%29&amp;rft.atitle=DIRAC+Family+Research&amp;rft.aulast=Dirac&amp;rft.aufirst=Gisela&amp;rft.au=Dirac%2C+Gisela&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dirac.ch%2FPaulDirac.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFPeierls_R1960">Peierls R (1960). "Wolfgang Ernst Pauli, 1900-1958". <i>Biographical memoirs of fellows of the Royal Society</i> (Royal Society (Great Britain)) <b>5</b>: 174–92. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frsbm.1960.0014" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frsbm.1960.0014" rel="nofollow">10.1098/rsbm.1960.0014</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Wolfgang+Ernst+Pauli%2C+1900-1958&amp;rft.jtitle=Biographical+memoirs+of+fellows+of+the+Royal+Society&amp;rft.aulast=Peierls+R&amp;rft.au=Peierls+R&amp;rft.date=1960&amp;rft.volume=5&amp;rft.pages=174%E2%80%9392&amp;rft.pub=Royal+Society+%28Great+Britain%29&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1098%2Frsbm.1960.0014&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKnowlson1996">Knowlson, James (1996). <i>Damned to Fame: The Life of Samuel Beckett</i>. London: Bloomsbury. p.&#160;79. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0747527199" class="internal">ISBN 0747527199</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Damned+to+Fame%3A+The+Life+of+Samuel+Beckett&amp;rft.aulast=Knowlson&amp;rft.aufirst=James&amp;rft.au=Knowlson%2C+James&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B79&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury&amp;rft.isbn=0747527199&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Laconic_phrase"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
